column5: My group is making the trip to Woman River June 1st. I would love to hear how everyone is doing on various bodies of water in the area and what they are biting on... Based on responses I can make modifications to the 40lb box prior to our trip.~RyanMadison, WI
Reports i have heard are the usual jig and minnow bite shallow. We are heading up to ear falls June 1st as well.
Jig and Minnow/Leech- shallow bite 4-8ft, fish are scattered right now. We would pick up a few here and there but not stacked up like usual
Knox- Wondering if you were fishing river system or larger body of water?
